item.title: [HIVE-22149] Metastore: Unify codahale metrics.log json structure between hiveserver2 and metastore services
item.description:
While fixing HIVE-22140 I found some really annoying differences between the codahale metric file structures between hiveserver2 and metastore, e.g.

open_connections: can be found in "counters" for hs2, but in "gauges" for ms
threads count: it's a proper "threads.count" for hs2, but a really ambiguous "count" for ms

so I realized that "memory." and "threads." prefix is completely absent in ms metrics file, which is misleading
item.summary: Metastore: Unify codahale metrics.log json structure between hiveserver2 and metastore services

status.description: The issue is considered finished, the resolution is correct. Issues which are not closed can be reopened.

+1 pending tests
I don't know about anything which might build upon these values; abstractdog do you know any?

e.g. Cloudera Manager relies on codahale metrics, and I faced a situation where I had to decide whether I'll change CM code in order to integrate to metastore service properly or unify these keys with the corresponding keys in hiveserver2 metric file (I did the latter)

unfortunately, as standalone-metastore should be able to be built independently from other parts of hive, I cannot refactor this logic to a common place
I see; yes....we have more and more chicken-egg problems...would putting the common part under standalone-metastore/common would be odd?

+1 overall
